text: Deaths in care homes are up 81% since the start of the Covid-19 vaccination rollout.
In the United Kingdom, 81% of COVID-19 deaths are among the vaccinated.
Over 70% of Covid-19 deaths are now in vaccinated people in the UK.
In the United Kingdom, 70-plus percent of the people who die now from COVID are fully vaccinated.
In England, COVID-19 vaccinated children are 4,423% more likely to die of any cause and 13,633% more likely to die of COVID-19 than unvaccinated children.
PHE released a report revealing 62% of Covid-19 deaths are people who have been vaccinated.
In England, official data shows children are up to 52 times more likely to die following COVID-19 vaccination than unvaccinated children.
Throughout Europe, the USA, the UK and Australia, medicine regulators have received reports of 77,068 deaths due to Covid-19 vaccination.
Most Covid-19 deaths in England are in the vaccinated
